=Social Proof #This demonstrates Social Proof—people look to others' actions to guide their own behavior, especially "similar others" (guests in the same room). The message shifted from generic request to showing what peers do.
~Unity #Unity involves shared group identity. While related, the hotel study specifically demonstrates Social Proof through showing peer behavior.
}

